      "rationale": "Simulation setup independently reviewed by a second PhD-level analyst using a 47-item checklist covering geometry import, material property assignments, contact pair definitions, boundary conditions, and load application. No critical errors identified; two minor documentation gaps corrected prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic material model with isotropic hardening; frictional contact at screw-rod interface; model form supported by literature and prior FDA validation studies.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V) selected based on published tensile coupon data and prior FDA CDRH internal validation studies. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod and rod-block interfaces captures load transfer mechanism consistent with physical understanding. Model form uncertainty assessed as low given extensive prior use of this formulation for spinal implant simulation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific tensile coupon testing of same production lot as test constructs; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of production hardware.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.1 GPa) derived from tensile coupon testing of the same Ti-6Al-4V production lot used in bench testing. Screw and rod geometry digitized via coordinate measuring machine (CMM) with 5 μm accuracy. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=500); 95th-percentile QoI variation <4%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs from production lot; sample characterization including dimensional inspection and hardness testing.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production hardware. Each construct dimensionally inspected (CMM) and hardness-tested (Rockwell C). Coefficient of variation in yield strength across lot: 2.1%. Samples representative of production population."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span at least two load levels or two fixation configurations to characterize model behavior across the COU envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (10° caudal load application, standard UHMWPE blocks). Only one load condition explored due to resource constraints. This factor falls below the required level; accepted on the basis that the single condition is the clinically relevant worst-case scenario and all other factors meet or exceed requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and load application within measurement uncertainty; block compliance accounted for.",
      "rationale": "UHMWPE block geometry, screw insertion depth, and load application angle (10°) replicated in FEA to within 0.5 mm and 0.2° of measured test fixture dimensions. Block elastic compliance measured and incorporated as spring elements. Crosshead displacement corrected for machine compliance using manufacturer-supplied stiffness data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
